what is postman.:-
what is postman is a client tool send the pure http request to the server.
and testing Api's.
postman has set of http method to intersepct the REST API,by using GET,POST ,PIT,PATCH,DELETE...
and also ha different payloads which can be binded as header, and body content.


what is defference B/w REST & SOAP.:=>
***********************************
1.rest : Respresntational state transfer
1.soap : simple object Access protocal


2.Rest : uses lower bandwith
2.Soap : uses Higher Bandwith

3.Rest : its follows web-standards related http protocal
3.Soap : its follows XML structure and conventions.based on Envelope and web standards.

4. REST : lower security
4.soap : Higher security

5.Rest : Easy to handle, easy to deserialise and serialise
5.Soap : very difficult to handle,

6. Rest : data representation is  in json,yml
6. soap : data representation is  in XML

Api Related terms:-
**********************
=>1. http method : these are set of method which are defined to perform some
unique operation
in rest Api 
http methds are reqivalent DB operation

C : create the data HTTP/1.1 POST
R : read the data HTTP/1.1 GET 
U : update the data HTTP/1.1 PUT AND PATCH
			PUT : full update
			PATCH : partial update
D : Delete the data HTTP/1.1 DELETE

HTTP has two version 1.1 and 2.1
headers :- are the type of payload (infometion) attached to request before data .
		headers con contain infometion like ,http satus : 200, or 404, 500
		header has content Information like content-type :text/html content-type:
		appliction/json ,content-type:Image:jpeg all these are called MIME type
		header has allowed methds : GET,POST,....
		header con be used to check if request are Authenitic or not
		header con be used to enable core policy (cotent origin request security policy)
 
Body Content :- it refers to form data , supplied from ,or any client like postman 
				type of body data
				1.formdata : form
				2.urlencoded : data
				3.www-encoded data
				4.raw data : json
				
				
